{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "On the front end, a user-friendly multi-PDF chatbot tool (MedDoc-Bot) was constructed with Streamlit V1.30 [13], a Python-based web application tool for machine learning and data science.",
    "This enables users to upload single or multiple PDF documents to the interface.",
    "A single prompt can trigger a search for relevant information across all uploaded PDFs and provide responses based on the selected LLMs' capabilities.",
    "The backend utilizes LangChain-a framework designed for language-driven applications for document processing [14].",
    "In our clinical application, we evaluated the performance of each model by interpreting the ESC hypertension guidelines for children and adolescents [2]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "On the front end, a user-friendly multi-PDF chatbot tool (MedDoc-Bot) was constructed with Streamlit V1.30 [13], a Python-based web application tool for machine learning and data science.",
    "The backend utilizes LangChain-a framework designed for language-driven applications for document processing [14].",
    "In our clinical application, we evaluated the performance of each model by interpreting the ESC hypertension guidelines for children and adolescents [2]."
